<paragraph id="8BC91A463C69AE2C5234FEBFEF00C6DF" blockId="8.[264,1324,284,790]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Bionomics. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7661C53C69AE2C52C0FEBFEF26C66C" box="[460,802,284,309]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singaporensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B902C6543C69AE2C52C0FEBFEF26C66C" box="[460,802,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Chersodromia singaporensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2317B2F3C69AE2C503CFEBFEF95C66F" box="[816,913,284,310]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
was only found on white sandy beaches or in mangroves with at least sandy patches. On one beach, specimens were found in the burrows of Ghost crabs, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7661C53C69AE2C517EFECFEED8C6DC" authority="Lamarck, 1801" authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1801" box="[626,732,364,389]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Ocypoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B902C6543C69AE2C517EFECFEED8C6DC" box="[626,732,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Ocypoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC91A463C69AE2C5234FE37ED5DC44F" blockId="8.[264,1324,284,790]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Remarks. The new species fits quite well within the definition of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C7661C53C69AE2C578FFE37E92FC6F4" box="[1155,1323,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speculifera">
<emphasis id="B902C6543C69AE2C578FFE37E92FC6F4" box="[1155,1323,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">C. speculifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE767B73C69AE2C5291FE1FEE4DC68F" author="Chvala" box="[413,585,444,470]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Chvala, M. (1977) Revision of Palaearctic species of the genus Chersodromia Walk. (Diptera, Empididae). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 39, 55 - 138." type="journal article" year="1977">
Chvála (
<number id="3DBE08613C69AE2C510CFE1FEE44C68F" box="[512,576,444,470]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1977.0">1977</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Among the Palaearctic species belonging to this group 
<taxonomicName id="4C7661C53C69AE2C57D0FE1FED83C6A4" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singaporensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B902C6543C69AE2C57D0FE1FED83C6A4" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">C. singaporensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2317B2F3C69AE2C5283FE47EDEEC6A7" box="[399,490,484,510]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C7661C53C69AE2C5161FE47EF4CC6A7" authority="Chvala" authorityName="Chvala" box="[621,840,484,510]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipes">
<emphasis id="B902C6543C69AE2C5161FE47EEEFC6A4" box="[621,747,484,509]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">C. flavipes</emphasis>
Chvála
</taxonomicName>
, known from the Atlantic coast of 
<collectingCountry id="F3615AD63C69AE2C57EEFE47E92DC6A7" box="[1250,1321,484,510]" name="Spain" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Spain</collectingCountry>
. However, there are three species described from 
<collectingCountry id="F3615AD63C69AE2C5052FDAFE84CC57F" box="[862,1096,524,550]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE767B73C69AE2C5757FDAFE91AC57F" author="Grootaert" box="[1115,1310,524,550]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Grootaert, P. (1992) New species of the genus Chersodromia Walker (Diptera Empidoidea Hybotidae) from the northern coast of Papua New Guinea. Bulletin and Annales de la Societe Royale Belge d'Entomologie, 128, 235 - 244." type="journal article" year="1992">
Grootaert, 
<number id="3DBE08613C69AE2C57D3FDAFE91AC57F" box="[1247,1310,524,550]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), which actually are more closely related to the new species sharing a single pair of vertical bristles, postpedicel with a distinct dorsoapical extension and a very similar structure of the male terminalia. All these species differ from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7661C53C69AE2C5046FD27E809C5C4" box="[842,1037,644,669]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singaporensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B902C6543C69AE2C5046FD27E809C5C4" box="[842,1037,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">C. singaporensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2317B2F3C69AE2C5718FD27E86AC5C7" box="[1044,1134,644,670]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by pale yellowish (
<taxonomicName id="4C7661C53C69AE2C5232FD0FEE49C59F" authority="Grootaert" authorityName="Grootaert" box="[318,589,684,710]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipyga">
<emphasis id="B902C6543C69AE2C5232FD0FEDD4C59C" box="[318,464,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">C. flavipyga</emphasis>
Grootaert
</taxonomicName>
) or yellowish­white (
<taxonomicName id="4C7661C53C69AE2C505EFD0FE833C59F" authority="Grootaert" authorityName="Grootaert" box="[850,1079,684,710]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micra">
<emphasis id="B902C6543C69AE2C505EFD0FEFBFC59C" box="[850,955,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">C. micra</emphasis>
Grootaert
</taxonomicName>
) to pale whitish (
<taxonomicName id="4C7661C53C69AE2C561CFD0FEDFCC5B7" authority="Grootaert" authorityName="Grootaert" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripyga">
<emphasis id="B902C6543C69AE2C561CFD0FED7EC5B4" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">C. nigripyga</emphasis>
Grootaert
</taxonomicName>
) palpus and by the lack of a presutural supra­alar (= posthumeral) bristle.
</paragraph>
